result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Timothy D. Wahls was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

Defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program - not eligible for release to Extended Supervision until having served no less than 42 months of the term of Initial Confinement. Defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Concurrent with: Any existing sentence.

superMiscConds.notes: The defendant is ordered to authorize the Department of Corrections to collect from the defendant's wages and from other moneys held in the defendant's prisoner's account, an amount or percentage the department determines is reasonable for payment to victims/governmental agencies.  If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision to the Department of Corrections. In the event the defendant will discharge or is revoked from extended supervision with outstanding obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the Court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement action will be used to collect the debt.
Same repayment conditions as noted above for the fine/costs.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license for the manner of operation.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 10:45 AM: Defendant Timothy D. Wahls in court, in custody. Attorney Robert N Forseth in court for Timothy D. Wahls. Attorney Matthew R. Leusink in court for State of Wisconsin. Amended Information filed. DE does not object to its filing. Receipt admitted - Reading waived. Defendant advised of potential punishment. Counts 2, 3, 4, 5, & 6 - DRI. Count 7 - Dismissed Outright. Statement by the DE. Statement by the Court. Court orders: 9 1/2 year term of imprisonment - bifurcated sentence - 4 1/2 years IC/5 years ES, concurrent to any other sentence. 158 days CFTS. Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. Defendant is not eligible for release to ES until having served no less than 42 months of IC. ES conditions: $1000 fine plus costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. $42.50 blood draw fee. AODA and follow through. The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license for the manner of operation. Lifetime DL revocation/3 year IID. OWI Assessment. Appeal rights given.
